history.content:
These three are all core courses in their respective areas. I wouldn't recommend do this unless you are super intelligent. However, that being said, given that none of these three are design electives, the workload would not be terribly high, but the concepts would be a little hard if all done in one semester.

Another response: I think you should definitely do it to get a feeling of different areas and see which one you want to explore more. All three are important but the workload I think is okay.
